title: Live coverage: SpaceX to launch 21 Starlink satellites on Falcon 9 rocket return to flight mission
summary: The mission is the first for SpaceX since a landing mishap caused it to lose its most flown Falcon 9 booster. Liftoff is set for 9:58 p.m. PDT (12:58 a.m. EDT, 0458 UTC).

title: SpaceX Falcon 9 regains flight approval operations from FAA

title: Polaris Dawn on hold; SpaceX booster fails on landing
summary: Another busy week of spaceflight activities contained a landing failure of a Falcon 9 booster for the first time in over three years. Looking forward, Falcon 9 could launch up to five launches this week, including the Polaris Dawn mission, whose private crew will conduct an inspiring mission profile. However, that has been delayed due to an unacceptable splashdown forecast. Then, other SpaceX missions include up to three Starlink flights and another set of Starshield satellites to low-Earth orbit (LEO) for the National Reconnaissance Office.

title: Launch Roundup: Polaris Dawn aims high, Starlink launches continue
summary: A total of five flights are on the worldwide launch manifest for this week. Most notable is the launch of a SpaceX Falcon 9 with the Polaris Dawn mission. A modified Crew Dragon capsule will carry four astronauts into the highest orbit a crewed mission has flown in since the Gemini missions.
